2. The ANSI-C Quoting (The "Nuclear" Option)
If standard quoting fails, Bash supports $'...' strings. This allows you to escape characters using backslashes effectively before they even reach nmcli.

Bash
nmcli device wifi connect $'Leviathan\'s Network' password "your_password"
3. Using the BSSID (The Fail-Proof Way)
If the SSID name is giving you too much grief, stop using the name entirely. Every router has a unique hardware address (BSSID). This bypasses the string-parsing issue completely.

